Step 1: To start a project in django you need to install python and the first step will be
    Command : pip install django (This will install django package to your system)

Step 2: For creating a project in django
    Command: django-admin startproject basic (basic is name of project and user can choose any as per their wish)

Step 3: For creating an app in the project
    Command: django-admin startapp trial (trial is name of app and can be changed as user choice)

Step 4: Make migration
    {check your file directory before using manage.py // in this case type cd basic}
    Command: python manage.py migrate

Step 5: Activate Admin panel
    Command: python manage.py createsuperuser
    {this gives acess to the admin panel}
    {Ctrl + c is used to break the command line}

Step 6: To run the project in server
    Command: python manage.py runserver
    { http://127.0.0.1:8000/ this lead to our homepage
        http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/login/?next=/admin/ this is url for admin login panel}

